Section 13 (Remote Network Interaction) note for users:

If you modify this program and provide it as a network-accessible
service to users (e.g. hosting your own kvendra-platform instance and
exposing it via HTTP to third parties), AGPL section 13 requires you
to offer the corresponding source code of your modified version to
those users. See https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html#section13
for the canonical legal text.

The Kvendra commercial product (kvendra-enterprise) is a separate,
proprietary codebase owned by the same legal entity and is NOT
governed by this AGPL license. See ADR-KVD-004 (Open Core licensing)
and ADR-KVD-023 (boundary motor vs operación SaaS).
